# RabbitMQ Erlang cookie — cluster shared secret (Profile B/C HA).
# ADR-057 PR-B2.5.
#
# Used to authenticate inter-node Erlang RPC calls within a
# RabbitMQ cluster. Single-node deploys (Profile A — Z-book)
# don't NEED this populated, but the chart still renders a
# Secret with it so future clustering enablement is a values-
# only change.
#
# 1. Generate a strong random cookie (`openssl rand -base64 32`).
# 2. Save as ./secrets/rabbitmq_erlang_cookie.txt (gitignored).
# 3. Run `make k8s-bootstrap-secrets`. Lands at:
#    - Vault: kv/audittrace/rabbitmq/admin (key: erlang_cookie)
#    - k8s Secret: <release>-rabbitmq (key: rabbitmq-erlang-cookie)
REPLACE_WITH_STRONG_RANDOM_COOKIE
